‼️🚨PLEASE READ CAPTION ‼️🚨 I am not typically one for New Year’s resolutions. In fact, New Years is my most dreaded days of the year. I typically feel as though it creates a lot of stress, pressure and comparison. I strongly believe you can start your “ New Year”’ and new habits any day of the year.

This year hit a little different due to some unexpected hard circumstances which forced me to start new and from scratch which happened to be at the New Year. 

So with some shifts in my life and new focuses ahead, I thought I would share what this year is going to look like which will also be a shift in my content.

This is the year of ME. 🙋🏻‍♀️🖤Focusing on my well-being, mindset, health and overall wellness by creating fresh starts, new focus’ on internal and external rebranding. 

✨New Place, New Chapter. Working this year on rebuilding my space, with a different vibe that will bring me joy, peace and create a sanctuary that is perfect for me. With the hardship of losing my last home and most belongings, I will be sharing home projects and focusing this year on my space and creating my perfect little sanctuary!

✨My health. Although content may shift, it is shifting to what is best for me, my body’s physical  health, and mental well being. 

✨ Real life , WFH, lounge and active wear. As you know, fashion is my entire life. Or I should say has been in the past. Although it is now shifting from what was my work and everyday, to now a passion. My dressed up, glam,  elevated statement pieces every day are no longer what is real and practical in my life. After the pandemic, I believe most of us like myself are now working from home and/or are much more casual and focused on lounge. I hope to bring elevated loungewear, athleisure and activewear that suits my everyday lifestyle to this platform more and to become more “ in the moment” with my content which hopefully will still inspire you! 

🥰🖤 I hope you stick around and join me on this journey to be more physically and mentally healthy and creating a lifestyle that will allow me to the best version of myself ( little by little) every day. 🥰🖤
